title: Measurement of double-differential cross sections of charged particle emission reactions for nat-Zr, 27Al, and nat-Ti by incident dt neutrons

and nat-Ti by incident dt neutrons

x4freetext: The d-beam energy was 300 keV and the intensity
was 5 mA. A sample transport system of six
pneumatic tubes provided irradiation positions giving
monochromatic neutrons of 13.4-14.9 MeV. Another tube
was put at -105 deg to check the symmetry of the
system. The irradiation positions was about 15 cm from
the tritium target. An additional tube set at -22.5
deg and at 1.5 cm distance was used when strong
activities were required. The transfer time was about
NE213 scintillation detector for neutron flux
Corrections are made for the Broadening function of
angular resolution, for energy loss of the charged
particles in sample for every angle of measurements
